column45: No rain in last 24 hours, wind became light onshore
No rain in last 24 hours, wind became light onshore
VOG and haze, 1 fisherman north of sampling
Peter Martin engaged in conversation about WQ. Wanted to know how cesspools affect WQ.
Team noted that temp on DO probe 0.2 C higher than salinity probe.  This is within tolerance.
Another encounter with Peter Martin asking about water quality data in the Wahikuli region.  Esp nutrient data.
Surfer asked questions about water quality
Lahaina fire 5 days previous of date. Blank pre-sample a little high.
Kayak tour group at site - 4 kayaks in the water and 5 on land about to launch
Light drizzle encountered, lid for bucket used
Salinity at OPM was above 35.0 on second test
Took 4th turbidity reading at OPM since 3rd was greater over 20% difference with the first two readings.
OCO - Did 2nd reading of salinity - value was the same
OUB - Did 2nd reading of salinity - value was 35.9
Had trouble getting D.O probe reading to pop up a few times but eventually it worked
All presampling tested a little high, Salinity testing higher than normal range
Rain started at end of sampling
Very Windy, white caps, stinging sand
2100Q struggled to turn on during pre-sample. We replaced the batteries.
First 2 sites - read temperature from "DO" probe. Later noted "DO" temperature (at later sites) ran 0.2 degrees higher than salinity probe.
OPM - Followed net "tip" procedure repeatedly - for Blank - still read out of range - best reading recorded
OCO190829 - 4th reading 6.89 turbidity, testing done on side of road with traffic going by, may have caused vibration of car. Also, I may not have had arrow on jar lined up.
OPB - HQ40d sensors took a little time to connect properly at this site, and it also turned off in the middle of a read
OPP - Took 4th reading of Turbidity at this site after big truck passed during read.
new turbidity sample cell in use, first turbidity sample bottle was scratched, we used backup glass bottle. scratched cell discarded.
Heavy winds shaking car.  Turbidity reading verified.
No pH reading taken.  4th Turbidity reading 6.31 NTU
Fairly windy weather today - heavy cloud cover
Very Windy Day.  Showers OFF & ON
pretty rainy morning - misty all around

Meters and probes used were from the southside lab
OPM: calm, like mirror lake - did DO/ salinity 2 times (2nd reading: 5.27 mg/L, 78.2%)
OUB: surfers - no one within 100 yards
